As vice-president he will oversee the foundations' advocacy work in Washington and Brussels as well as provide strategic direction and oversight to the organisation's programme according to a statement issued on Friday."Patrick Gaspard's deep experience in policy and politics along with his energy and commitment to social justice are great assets to help further the Open Society Foundations' mission to build vibrant and tolerant democracies " said Chris Stone the foundation s president.Gaspard became the US ambassador to South Africa in 2013 and worked to strengthen civil society healthcare infrastructure and innovations in local governance. He also helped to connect South African entrepreneurs to US markets develop energy technologies and tackle wildlife trafficking the statement said.He worked previously in the White House office of political affairs and was also and adviser to President Barack Obama.The Open Society Foundations which promotes democracy works in more than 120 countries.